Variables:-
        Variables are containers used to store data values during the execution of a program.

Local Variables:-
        Declared inside method or block.
        Must be initialized before use.

public void show(){
    int age=25;//local variable
    System.out.println(age);
}

Instance Variables:-
        Declared inside the class,but outside the method.
        When object is created.

class student{
    String name;//Instance 
    int age;//instance
    public void show(){
        System.out.println(name+"is"+age+" years old.");
    }
}

Static Variables:-
        Declared with the static keyword.
        shared among all objects of the class.

class Student {
    static String school = "ABC School";  // static variable
}

syntax:-
dataType variableType;
dataType variableType=value;

Datatypes:-
        Data types specify the kind of data a variable can hold. They are divided into two categories.

1.Primitive Datatypes
2.Non Primitive Datatypes.

1.Primitive Datatypes:-
double price=99.99;
char c='A';
int x=123456;
short s=5000;
float f=5.5f;
long l=999999L;
byte b=100;
boolean b=true;

2.Non Primitive Datatypes:-
String name="Java";//string
int[] arr={1,2,3};//array
Student s=new Student();//classes
Runnable r=new Task();//interfaces

